A and B are both effective methods to keep cool outside, but they work in different ways.

Option B, sitting under a shade tree, is also an effective way to keep cool. Being in the shade reduces the amount of direct sunlight on your body, which can significantly lower your skin temperature. However, this method may not be as immediately effective as Option A, and it also depends on the availability of a shade tree.

A
